	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1089 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It is not wise to always avoid the aggro.&nbsp;&nbsp;You have defensive skills that mostly only go up through use: Defense, Dodge, Parry, Riposte.  Its okay to take some of the heat.  Just don't take all of it.<br><br>Pulling is very much a rogue thing.  Just don't pull with backstab.  Use a shuriken or throwing knife.  Low damage but gets the mobs attention just fine.  Even with deadly strike the most I ever hit a mob for with a shuriken is 30.  Sneak + Hide gets me safely within range.  Throw, turn and run.  Get back to the tanks.  Evade.  Tank will pick up the aggro very quickly.  I have even pulled with melee weapons and not had a major aggro problem.  Pull with poisons.  DOT's like Flesh Rot or Injected work well since the poison takes time to build up aggro from damage.  If your AC rating is up to snuff (at least 20 times your level) you should have little or no problem with pulling.<br><br>Slipskin Ashenheart</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
